theorem Topology.closure_interior_closure_eq_closure_of_isOpen
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X}
    (hA : IsOpen (A : Set X)) :
    closure (interior (closure (A : Set X))) = closure A := by
  -- We show the two inclusions separately.
  apply Set.Subset.antisymm
  · -- `⊆` direction
    have h₁ : (interior (closure (A : Set X)) : Set X) ⊆ closure A :=
      interior_subset
    exact closure_mono h₁
  · -- `⊇` direction
    -- For an open set `A`, we have `A ⊆ interior (closure A)` (i.e. `P3 A`).
    have h_sub : (A : Set X) ⊆ interior (closure A) := by
      have hP3 : Topology.P3 (X := X) A :=
        Topology.isOpen_P3 (X := X) (A := A) hA
      exact (hP3 : (A : Set X) ⊆ interior (closure A))
    -- Taking closures preserves inclusion.
    have h₂ : closure (A : Set X) ⊆ closure (interior (closure A)) :=
      closure_mono h_sub
    simpa using h₂
